Curtis Janssen's Home Page

Projects

     * The Massively Parallel Quantum Chemistry Program uses SC to
       implement quantum chemistry methods on distributed memory massively
       parallel machines.
     * The Scientific Computing Toolkit (SC) is a library of classes for
       implementing scientific programs in C++, with support for massively
       parallel machines.
     * The Second Quantization Symbol Manipulator derives equations using
       the second quantization formalism.
     * Performance optimization for scientific applications.
     * Diagnostics for correlated electronic structure methods
     * Use of multi-threading in parallel scientific applications

